{"comments":"CaseConvention - structural text casing conventions.\n\nUnlike TextTransform (which is visual-only rendering), CaseConvention\nrepresents **structural** transformations that modify the actual string\ncontent. These are used for:\n\n- Identifier generation (variable names, function names)\n- File naming conventions\n- API endpoint paths\n- Configuration keys\n- Database column names\n- CSS class names\n- URL slugs\n\n**Important distinction from TextTransform:**\n- TextTransform: Visual rendering, source preserved, CSS-based\n- CaseConvention: Structural change, modifies content, lossy\n\nCaseConvention transformations are generally **lossy** — converting\n\"hello world\" to \"helloWorld\" loses the space, and you cannot reliably\nrecover the original without additional context.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[99,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/CaseConvention.purs","start":[99,3]},"title":"CamelCase"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[103,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/CaseConvention.purs","start":[103,3]},"title":"PascalCase"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[107,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/CaseConvention.purs","start":[107,3]},"title":"SnakeCase"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[111,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/CaseConvention.purs","start":[111,3]},"title":"ScreamingSnakeCase"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[115,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/CaseConvention.purs","start":[115,3]},"title":"KebabCase"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[119,23]